@startuml seat_belt_override_to_warning_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Seat Belt Override To Warning Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> Router -> BCM -> CoreState / CLU)

actor "Driver / Passenger\n(Input Console)" as Occupant #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nVehicle > Belt Sim" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "INPUT_CONSOLE_ROUTER\nbelt toggle normalizer" as Router #FFF4CC
participant "BCM\nseat-belt state owner" as BCM #E8F7E8
participant "CoreState\nbelt warning mirrors" as CoreState #FCE8FF
participant "CLU\ncluster warning consumer" as CLU #E8F0FE

== Belt Toggle Input ==

Occupant -> Panel : Click DRV / PASS belt toggle
activate Panel
Panel -> Router : Test::driverBeltOff\nTest::passengerBeltOff
note right of Panel
Panel uses toggle-style belt simulation
instead of direct percentage input.
end note
deactivate Panel

== Router Override Derivation ==

activate Router
Router -> Router : refreshSeatBeltOverrideFromPanel()
Router -> Router : seatBeltOverride =\n(driverOff ? 1 : 0) +\n(passengerOff ? 2 : 0)
Router -> BCM : Test::driverBeltOff\nTest::passengerBeltOff\nTest::seatBeltOverride
note right of Router
Representative seams
- Test::driverBeltOff
- Test::passengerBeltOff
- Test::seatBeltOverride
end note
deactivate Router

== BCM Warning Ownership ==

activate BCM
BCM -> BCM : DriverSeatBelt = driverOff ? 0 : 1
BCM -> BCM : PassengerSeatBelt = passengerOff ? 0 : 1
BCM -> BCM : SeatBeltWarnLvl =\n(gDriveState > 0) ? 3 : 2\nwhen any front belt is off
BCM -> CoreState : driverSeatBelt\npassengerSeatBelt\nseatBeltWarnLvl
BCM -> CLU : frmSeatBeltStateMsg
note right of BCM
BCM is the effective owner of
front seat belt state and warning level.
end note
deactivate BCM

== Cluster Visibility ==

activate CLU
CLU -> CLU : consume seat-belt state frame\nwithin base cluster warning logic
CLU -> Panel : warning readback / cluster indication
deactivate CLU

note over Occupant, CLU
Representative runtime chain
1. Input_Console toggles driver/passenger belt-off state
2. Router compresses panel toggles into seatBeltOverride mirrors
3. BCM publishes seat-belt state and warning level
4. CLU consumes belt state for visible warning outcome
end note

@enduml
